started in 2007, but with rising inflation and more newcomers to B.C., including Ukrainian refugees, Beley says the charity is seeing rising demand for its services. The space offers protective gear - steel-toed boots, hard hats, high-visibility vests, coats, dress shirts, blouses, dresses, shoes and more for those who can''t afford them.
