ver the years, there is a vocal minority who consider pretty much any recreation of depiction of our past to be offensive because it inevitably shows objects and people from our colonial past.' || CHR(13) || CHR(10) || CHR(13) || CHR(10) || 'This minority seemed to have captured the views of the museum management, who announced in November 2021 that Old Town would disappear. A few months later, the B.C. government announced the entire museum would be closed for eight years while a new facility was built.' || CHR(13) || CHR(10) || CHR(13) || CHR(10) || 'Again, cue the harshly negative public reaction.' || CHR(13) || CHR(10) || CHR(13) || CHR(10) || 'The government backed down   the announcement that the replacement idea was on hold was one of John Horgan''s last major announcements as premier   and things went quiet, until February.' || CHR(13) || CHR(10) || CHR(13) || CHR(10) || 'After leaving the strong impression that Old Town had been torn down, the museum surprised many when it casually announced in February that, in fact, the exhibit was still largely intact.','Museum exhibit reopening is a victory for common sense','Newspaper',1,1,0,null,to_date('16-MAY-23','DD-MON-RR'),to_date('16-MAY-23','DD-MON-RR'),null,null,null,'column','Keith Baldrey','Keith Baldrey',null,null,null,0,0,null,to_date('01-JAN-70','DD-MON-RR'),null,null,null,0,'krypto',0,0,null,0,0,0,0,'jglass',0,1,0,null,0,0,0,0,null,null,null);
